  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do bottle caps work in Pokemon Sun / Moon?",
  "response": "In Pok\u00e9mon Sun and Moon, bottle caps are items that can be used to enhance your Pok\u00e9mon's individual values (IVs). Here's how they work:\n\n1. **Types of Bottle Caps:**\n   - **Bottle Cap:** A regular bottle cap can be used to maximize one IV of a Pok\u00e9mon.\n   - **Gold Bottle Cap:** A gold bottle cap can be used to maximize all six IVs of a Pok\u00e9mon.\n\n2. **Usage:**\n   - To use bottle caps, you need to visit the Pok\u00e9mon Hyper Training facility located in a house on the east side of the Battle Tree on Poni Island.\n   - At the Hyper Training facility, you can speak to the old man who will offer to hyper train your Pok\u00e9mon.\n   - If your Pok\u00e9mon has reached level 100, you can use bottle caps to hyper train it. A regular bottle cap will allow you to max out one IV of your choice, while a gold bottle cap will max out all six IVs.\n\n3. **Obtaining Bottle Caps:**\n   - **Bottle Caps:** You can obtain regular bottle caps through various means, such as participating in the Battle Royal, fishing with the throwable fishing rod (SOS battles), or receiving them as rewards from certain festivals.\n   - **Gold Bottle Caps:** Gold bottle caps are rarer and can be obtained through special events, such as completing certain missions in the Festival Plaza, or occasionally as rewards from the Battle Tree.\n\n4. **Benefits:**\n   - Hyper training with bottle caps allows you to improve your Pok\u00e9mon's stats without the need for breeding or searching for perfect IV Pok\u00e9mon, making it easier to prepare your team for competitive battles.\n\nUsing bottle caps is a strategic way to enhance your Pok\u00e9mon's performance, particularly in competitive play, where having high IVs can make a significant difference in battles.",
